The Olympic symbol, also known as the Olympic rings, consists of five interconnected rings of equal size, colored blue, yellow, black, green, and red, respectively, on a white background.

Meaning of the Olympic Rings
1. Unity of the Five Continents: The five rings represent the unity of the five continents of the world: Africa, Asia, Europe, Oceania, and the Americas.
2. International Solidarity: The interconnected rings symbolize international solidarity, friendship, and fair play among athletes from different parts of the world.
3. Olympic Spirit: The rings embody the Olympic spirit, which promotes unity, equality, and mutual respect among nations and athletes.

Color Significance
The colors of the rings were chosen because at least one of them appears on the flag of every nation in the world, symbolizing universality and inclusivity.
